===Decorations===
*[[Front Flying Clasp of the Luftwaffe|Front Flying Clasp of the ''Luftwaffe'']] in Gold with Pennant "1300"{{sfn|Berger|1999|p=105}}
*[[Pilot/Observer Badge]] in Gold with Diamonds (25 August 1944){{sfn|Berger|1999|p=105}}
*[[Iron Cross]] (1939)
** 2nd Class (17 December 1942){{sfn|Thomas|1997|p=249}}
** 1st Class (7 March 1943){{sfn|Thomas|1997|p=249}}
*[[Honour Goblet of the Luftwaffe|Honour Goblet of the ''Luftwaffe'']] (''Ehrenpokal der Luftwaffe'') on 13 September 1943 as ''[[Leutnant]]'' and pilot{{sfn|Patzwall|2008|p=95}}
*[[German Cross]] in Gold on 17 October 1943 as ''Leutnant'' in the III./''Jagdgeschwader'' 52{{sfn|Patzwall|Scherzer|2001|p=166}}
*[[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves, Swords and Diamonds]]
**Knight's Cross on 29 October 1943 as ''Leutnant'' and pilot in the 9./''Jagdgeschwader'' 52{{sfn|Fellgiebel|2000|p=214}}{{refn|According to Scherzer as pilot in the pilot in the 7./''Jagdgeschwader'' 52.{{sfn|Scherzer|2007|p=368}}|group="Note"}}
**420th Oak Leaves on 2 March 1944 as ''Leutnant'' and ''Staffelführer'' of the 9./''Jagdgeschwader'' 52{{sfn|Scherzer|2007|p=368}}{{sfn|Fellgiebel|2000|p=79}}
**75th Swords on 2 July 1944 as ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' and ''[[Staffelkapitän]]'' of the 9./''Jagdgeschwader'' 52{{sfn|Scherzer|2007|p=368}}{{sfn|Fellgiebel|2000|p=43}}
**18th Diamonds on 25 August 1944 as ''Oberleutnant'' and ''Staffelkapitän'' of the 9./''Jagdgeschwader'' 52{{sfn|Scherzer|2007|p=368}}{{sfn|Fellgiebel|2000|p=37}}
*Two named references in the ''[[Wehrmachtbericht]]'' (24&nbsp;August 1944 and 25&nbsp;August 1944){{sfn|Murawski|1962|pp=248–249}}

Hartmann had kept the whereabouts of his Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross secret from his captors during his time as a prisoner of war, claiming that he had thrown it away. The hiding place was in a small stream. His comrade [[Hans "Assi" Hahn]] managed to hide the Knight's Cross in a double bottom cigar box and smuggled it back to Germany when he was released from captivity.{{sfn|Maerz|2007|p=120}}

===Dates of rank===
Hartmann joined the military service in ''Wehrmacht'' on 1 October 1940. His first station was [[Neukuhren]] in [[East Prussia]], where he received his military [[basic training]] as a ''Luftwaffe'' recruit.{{sfn|Toliver|Constable|1985|pp=296–297}}
{|
! Wehrmacht
|-
| 1 April 1942: || ''[[Leutnant]]'' (second lieutenant){{sfn|Stockert|2007|p=40}}
|-
| 1 May 1944: || ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' (first lieutenant){{sfn|Stockert|2007|p=41}}
|-
| 1 September 1944: || ''[[Hauptmann]]'' (captain){{sfn|Stockert|2007|p=43}}
|-
| 8 May 1945: || ''[[Major (Germany)|Major]]'' (major){{refn|His promotion to ''Major'' on 8 May 1945 is unconfirmed. Hartmann himself, in a document dated 16 May 1945, used the rank ''Hauptmann''.{{sfn|Stockert|2007|p=43}}|group="Note"}}
|-
! Bundeswehr
|-
| 12 December 1960: || ''[[Oberstleutnant]]'' (lieutenant colonel){{sfn|Stockert|2007|p=44}}
|-
| 26 July 1967: || ''[[Oberst]]'' (colonel){{sfn|Stockert|2007|p=44}}
|}

